==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mainsail
<hw>Main"sail`</hw> <pr>(m⟦amac⟧n"s⟦amac⟧l`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>The principal sail in a ship or other
vessel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[They] hoised up the <qex>mainsail</qex> to the wind.</q>
<rj><qau> Acts xxvii. 40.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The <xex>mainsail</xex> of a ship is extended upon a
yard attached to the mainmast, and that of a sloop or schooner upon the
boom.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>main sequence</ent>⟦br⟧
